# IIO core (industrialio). The air unit has no button ladder (no adc-keys), but it reads two SoC
# sensors over IIO for telemetry: the SAR ADC (artosyn_adc, battery voltage on channel 1) and the
# on-die temperature sensor (artosyn_protemp). Both register IIO devices, so the core must be built
# in; trim.config disables it and this fragment re-enables it.
#
# No buffering: both drivers use one-shot INDIO_DIRECT_MODE reads, so the trigger/buffer
# infrastructure is dead weight.
#
# MERGE THIS AFTER trim.config. The goggle gets IIO via input.config (which also pulls in
# adc-keys/evdev for the keypad); the air needs only the core, so it lists this fragment instead.

CONFIG_IIO=y
# CONFIG_IIO_BUFFER is not set
# CONFIG_IIO_TRIGGERED_BUFFER is not set
